            . I am a <rs id="t18190526-116-viclabel642" type="occupation">slopseller</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18190526-116-victim1039 t18190526-116-viclabel642"></join>, and live in Shadwell. On the 19th of May, about ten o'clock, a man came into the shop to look at some shoes - another man, who appeared to belong to him, stood at the door. The man at the door said go the rig, twice. In about a minute I went out, and saw the prisoner about two doors off, concealing a pair of shoes under his apron. I collared him, and the other two ran away.</p>
               <p>(Property produced and sworn to.)</p>
               <p>Prisoner's Defence. I found them.</p>
